**The Dialectical Unity of Thesis, to Synthesis**: Hegel's most iconic concept is the dialectical process, I call it "unity in opposites."
He believed that opposing forces or ideas (thesis and antithesis) ultimately merge to form a higher level of understanding (synthesis).
